    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Cron`}</strong>{` is one of the most useful utility that you can find in any Unix-like operating system.  `}<br />{`
It is used to schedule commands at a specific time. These scheduled commands or tasks are known as `}<strong parentName="p">{`Cron Jobs`}</strong>{`. `}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "adding-a-cron-job"
    }}>{`Adding a Cron Job`}</h2>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "via-cloudpanel"
    }}>{`Via CloudPanel`}</h3>
    <p>{`To add a `}<strong parentName="p">{`Cron Job`}</strong>{` click on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Add Cron Job`}</strong>{` top right.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cron-jobs/new_cron_job.png')} /> <br /> <br />
    <p>{`Select a `}<strong parentName="p">{`Template`}</strong>{` that prefills the fields `}<strong parentName="p">{`Minute`}</strong>{`, `}<strong parentName="p">{`Hour`}</strong>{`, `}<strong parentName="p">{`Day`}</strong>{`, `}<strong parentName="p">{`Month`}</strong>{`, and `}<strong parentName="p">{`Weekday`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`Enter the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Command`}</strong>{` and select the user as which the cron job will be executed.`}</p>
    <div {...{
      "className": "admonition admonition-warning alert alert--danger"
    }}><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-heading"
      }}><h5 parentName="div"><span parentName="h5" {...{
            "className": "admonition-icon"
          }}><svg parentName="span" {...{
              "xmlns": "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg",
              "width": "12",
              "height": "16",
              "viewBox": "0 0 12 16"
            }}><path parentName="svg" {...{
                "fillRule": "evenodd",
                "d": "M5.05.31c.81 2.17.41 3.38-.52 4.31C3.55 5.67 1.98 6.45.9 7.98c-1.45 2.05-1.7 6.53 3.53 7.7-2.2-1.16-2.67-4.52-.3-6.61-.61 2.03.53 3.33 1.94 2.86 1.39-.47 2.3.53 2.27 1.67-.02.78-.31 1.44-1.13 1.81 3.42-.59 4.78-3.42 4.78-5.56 0-2.84-2.53-3.22-1.25-5.61-1.52.13-2.03 1.13-1.89 2.75.09 1.08-1.02 1.8-1.86 1.33-.67-.41-.66-1.19-.06-1.78C8.18 5.31 8.68 2.45 5.05.32L5.03.3l.02.01z"
              }}></path></svg></span>{`Permissions`}</h5></div><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-content"
      }}><p parentName="div">{`Running the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Cron Job`}</strong>{` as the right user is very important. Running as the right user will prevent permission issues e.g.,
if your script is reading and writing files.`}</p></div></div>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "via-command-line"
    }}>{`Via Command Line`}</h3>
    <p>{`The standard linux way to configure `}<strong parentName="p">{`Cron Jobs`}</strong>{` on the command line can be used as well.`}</p>
    <p>{`1) Login via `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "users#ssh-login"
      }}>{`SSH`}</a>{` with the user who should run the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Cron Job`}</strong>{` e.g. `}<strong parentName="p">{`john-ssh`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`2) Enter the following command to edit `}<strong parentName="p">{`Cron Jobs`}</strong>{`:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`crontab -e
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`3) Enter your `}<strong parentName="p">{`Cron Job`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`On the following `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://tecadmin.net/crontab-in-linux-with-20-examples-of-cron-schedule/"
      }}>{`site`}</a>{`, you find some useful
examples of how to configure them.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "deleting-a-cron-job"
    }}>{`Deleting a Cron Job`}</h2>
    <p>{`On the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Cron Jobs`}</strong>{` overview site, you can delete a `}<strong parentName="p">{`Cron Job`}</strong>{` by clicking on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Delete`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cron-jobs/delete_cron_job.png')} /> 
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "settings"
    }}>{`Settings`}</h2>
    <p>{`In the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Settings`}</strong>{`, you can enter an email address to receive the output every time the cron job runs.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/cron-jobs/mailto_settings.png')} />
    </MDXLayout>;
}

